    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect ciphering key sequence number decoding for single octet IEIs\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_ciphering_key_sequence_number` function was incorrectly handling single octet IEIs like 0x80. It was attempting to extract both the IEI and ciphering key sequence number from the same byte, which is incorrect according to 3GPP TS 24.008. This caused the function to read wrong values and potentially fail IEI validation.\n\nThis fix properly separates IEI handling from data extraction for single octet IEIs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/CipheringKeySequenceNumber.c`: \n  * Fixed IEI validation to properly check single octet IEIs\n  * Separated IEI byte from data byte when IEI is present\n  * Updated encoding function to properly handle IEI placement\n  * Added dynamic length checking based on IEI presence\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/CipheringKeySequenceNumber.h`: \n  * Updated maximum length constant to account for IEI byte\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing Tracking Area Update Request messages containing the GPRS ciphering key sequence number IEI (0x80), the decoder would incorrectly validate the IEI and extract garbage values for the sequence number. This could be observed as:\n- Failed IEI validation errors in the logs\n- Incorrect ciphering key sequence numbers being processed\n- Potential message decoding failures in TAU procedures\n\nThe issue manifests when UE includes ciphering key sequence number information in TAU requests, causing the network to incorrectly process the security parameters.\n"
}